# Modern UI standards

These rules enforce baseline mobile usability and polish for interactive UI work.

## 1) Card depth must use platform elevation/shadow

- Do not create depth with border-only cards.
- Card-like surfaces should include:
  - Android: `elevation`
  - iOS: `shadowColor`, `shadowOffset`, `shadowOpacity`, `shadowRadius`

```tsx
// ❌ BAD: Border-only card depth
const styles = StyleSheet.create({
  card: {
    backgroundColor: colors.surface,
    borderWidth: 1,
    borderColor: colors.border,
    borderRadius: radius.card,
  },
});
```

```tsx
// ✅ GOOD: Platform-aware card depth
const styles = StyleSheet.create({
  card: {
    backgroundColor: colors.surface,
    borderWidth: 1,
    borderColor: colors.border,
    borderRadius: radius.card,
    elevation: 3, // Android
    shadowColor: "#000", // iOS
    shadowOffset: { width: 0, height: 3 },
    shadowOpacity: 0.2,
    shadowRadius: 6,
  },
});
```

## 2) Interactive controls need at least 44x44 touch area

- Buttons, chips, icon buttons, and any pressable control must provide a minimum touch target of `44x44`.
- Use size styles (`minWidth`, `minHeight`) and/or `hitSlop` if visual size must stay compact.

```tsx
// ❌ BAD: Touch area is too small
<Pressable style={{ paddingHorizontal: 8, paddingVertical: 6 }}>
  <Text>Katıl</Text>
</Pressable>
```

```tsx
// ✅ GOOD: Meets minimum touch target
<Pressable
  hitSlop={4}
  style={{
    minWidth: 44,
    minHeight: 44,
    paddingHorizontal: 12,
    justifyContent: "center",
    alignItems: "center",
  }}
>
  <Text>Katıl</Text>
</Pressable>
```

## 3) State changes must animate smoothly

- For visual state changes (for example `Loading -> Success`), use smooth transition animation.
- Use `LayoutAnimation` or `react-native-reanimated` APIs (`withTiming`, `withSpring`, layout transitions).
- Avoid abrupt UI swaps with no transition.

```tsx
// ❌ BAD: Abrupt state switch
return isLoading ? <ActivityIndicator /> : <SuccessView />;
```

```tsx
// ✅ GOOD: Animated transition
LayoutAnimation.configureNext(LayoutAnimation.Presets.easeInEaseOut);
setIsLoading(false);
```

Apply these checks whenever touching UI interactions, cards, or async status-driven surfaces.
